\frac{1}{4 \sqrt{ |1-x|}} & \text{if} \ x\in [0,2] \\ 
 0 & \text{otherwise}\end{cases}$$ Could someone kindly explain to me how to handle the if/else portion when calculating an inverse? I have managed to compute that if $y = f(x)$ then $$x = 1 - \frac{1}{16y^2}$$   or $$x = 1 + \frac{1}{16y^2}$$ However, I believe it's the last step of putting it altogether that I can't pull off.
